column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR

Choppy waves- scattered clouds- .25" of rain earlier today.  Particulate matter prevalent.  No ice and no algal blooms observed.  The water is dark olive green.  At 13:40 100 yards off dock secchi reading was 12'. Cameron monitored with Jim Saladino.
Light wind from north- northeast- slight ripples.  Last rainfall about 1 1/2" on 6/18.  Cameron monitored with Drury and Kevin Davis.
The water is brownish green.  Choppy and very cloudy.  Particulate matter observed.
The water is choppy.  Sunny.  The water is olive green.
Partly cloudy- 75 degrees and good breeze for sailing.  Cameron monitored with Lola Equiguren.
The water is dark olive green.  Cameron monitored with Paul Withineton.
S wind- slightly choppy- partly cloudy but bright- 70 F
Bright sun- E breeze- lake calm
Partly cloudy- choppy- particulate matter through-out water column
Lake turned over- temp. @ surf.-40' 58 F- 56' 52 F- 60'-70' 50 F- 80'-bottom 49 F.
Sunny- light breeze- no boating activity
Cottonwood shedding is creating a mess.
Hazy sun- light wind- but this was the best condition to take reading in the last two weeks.  Lake has turned over.
Water temp: at surface 55- at 90' 46 degrees.
With all of the rain- water clarity reduced.
Light particulate content.  Cloudy sky- minor wave action.
Water level very low- usual level this time of year 98.00.  This is already causing problems + level usually drops during the summer.

Water level is extremely low for this time of the year.  Wis. valley improvement co. badly managed the dam in this area.  Long lake- big sand and the creek that joins them are very low.  This could effect us all year.  Could cause problems
Lake level very low causing problems of all sorts.
First measurement.  Tested at 85'.  Day partly cloudy-slight breeze.
Clear skies- light breeze- light rain in a.m.
Lake level still very low- effecting swimming- boating - fishing- etc.
Lake level is very low- I would suggest the Department of Natural Resources look into the possibility of mis-management of the dam by the Wisconsin valley improvement assoc.
Choppy- cloudy- small clumps of bright green algae near shore never seen before.
Sunny with few clouds and light breeze.  Beautiful.  Lake level:  Stable from last reading
Sunny- blue sky- breezy.  Note: this is the last report until spring 1995. Water level: Up 6" since 9/8 reading
Weather very warm.  Quite a lot of floating algae.
Water level very high. water turbidity also the highest I can remember. normal secchi reading this time of year 11'-12'
Water color is neither green or brown but somewhere in between.
Algae seems to be more abundant this year.
Water seems dirtier than in other years
Beautiful- sunny- scattered clouds- wind 10 mph s- ducks/loons active.
Overcast- wind 10 mph w.  Loons active
Scattered clouds- 5 mph w. 2 adult- 1 young loon.
Partly cloudy- wind 5 mph s- water clarity terrific.
Partly cloudy- light breeze.  Loons active.
Very overcast- light wind. 3 loons flying.
Sunny with clouds. 5 mph breeze. gulls- loons- ducks active.
Cloudy and there is a mild breeze.
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED SAMPLE 0-2M
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
Partly cloudy- 5-10 mph wind- and the loons are active.
Sunny and there is a light breeze.
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
Sunny with a light breeze.  The loons are active- and there are 10 mergansers and one beaver.
Sunny with a light breeze.  There are loons and cormorants.
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
AT POINT OF MAXIMUM DEPTH- INTEGRATED 0-2M
Light wind- sunny- high clouds.  Poplar cotton on lake.  Pollen floating.  Rain yesterday.
Windy- partly cloudy- saw the pair of loons.
Beautiful day- good day for boating.
Dozen boats on lake- large clouds / hazy.  Slight chop on water.  Sunny.
Stormy last night.  Today: hot/sunny 93 F.  Beautiful day on lake.
Saw total of 5 loons on lake.
Slight chop on water.  Light blue sky.  High clouds.  85 F.  Water level lower.
Sunny- light wind.  Lots of boating traffic.  Beautiful day.  Very little waterfowl.
Cooler- 70 F.  Partly cloudy- slight chop on water.
Kayakers on lake.  Lots of boat traffic.  Gorgeous day.
Cloudy- saw a family of mergansers and bald eagle in nest.
Sunny- light clouds.  Nice day to be on lake.
Partly cloudy.  Choppy/windy.  Light boat traffic.
lake down about 8-10" from normal levels this time of year
saw one pair of loons- slight bloom on lake
Nice evening for a boat ride- saw both pairs of loons
Evidence of many more people using lake for upcoming holiday
Nice Day- warm- several boats on lake- saw 2 pairs of loons
Another nice day- great boat ride- Kayakers on lake- saw 2 pair of loons
Evidence of Eurasian water milfoil on Dam end of lake
Lake level still dropping- down 12-15" minimum
Slightly windy with slight wave action- saw immature eagle at nest
Absolutely gorgeous! Sunny. Lake very calm. Like glass at times- total of 5 loons
working on lake with floating loon nest
slightly overcast- level of water extremely low- windy at times.
great fall day- slight breeze- light clouds- mid 50's clear and crisp
Cool in the morning (45 F).  64 F in the afternoon.  Loon raft active.  Skiing- boating- fishing.  Overcast.
Windy.  Storm moving in.  60 F.  Bloom on water's surface.  Not a good day for boating.
Saw activity on loon raft.  Sunny.  Great day to be on lake.  Water level low.
Slight chop on water.  Loon raft vacated.  2 loons with baby.  Eagle in nest by thoroughfare.
80 F.  Great day on lake.  Light boat traffic.  Adult loon with baby.
Sunny- high 70s.  Beautiful day.  People boating- skiing- fishing.  Total 4 loons.
Weather ominus.  Hot and humid earlier (93 F).  Very dark clouds.
Lake getting lower.  Tough getting boat out.  High upper 70s.  Nice day!
Lots of boaters.  Many kayaks- skiiers.  Saw 2 eagles.  Around 80 F.
Lake level frustratingly low.  No loons or eagles sighted.  Lots of boaters- skiiers- swimmers.
Need rain!  Slightly choppy water.  Mid 70s.  Overcast.
Moving boat to deeper water.  Cool- rainy.  Only boat out at this time.
Mid 70s.  Overcast.  Still lots of boaters on the lake.  Saw eagle in pine tree.
Pulling out boat.  Low water levels disturbing.  Overcast.  Colors of trees beautiful.
Sunny- very pleasant. Light clouds- upper 60s. Loon on raft
Windy- water very choppy- very few boats. Mid 60s. Saw loons.
Extremely windy. Rain in past 24 hours. No other boats on lake.
70s. WIndy. Rain last night. Saw loons on nest. A few boats. Dark clouds to NW.
70s. Hard to see secchi due to waves. Windy but nice day. Many boats. 2 baby loons
Calm- sunny. Upper 70s- skiers and boaters. Eagle @ nest by thoroughfare.
Great day- nieces tubing. Close to 80F- Saw 2 pairs of loons and 2 baby loons.
Long Lake regatta. Windy- water choppy. Lots of activity entire lake. Sunny.
Dark clouds- light rain heading in. Not much wildlife. 80F. Few boaters.
Very choppy and windy. Noticed more Eurasian Water Milfoil than usual. Upper 60s.
Beautiful day. Upper 70s- saw eagles- osprey- and loons.
Slight wind- not too many boats. Saw loons with babies
Taking out boat. Very overcast. Musky fisherman trolling. Fall colors - Beautiful!
Low 50s- partly sunny- brisk winds.  Saw loons by thorofare.
Sunny- windy- slight chop/waves.  Bald eagle in nest.
Windy- choppy waters- overcast- few boats.  Loons on nest/raft.
Beautiful afternoon.  Saw loons with 2 babies.  Full tour of lake.
Mid 60s- slight rain- no wildlife- no other boats.  Dark clouds.
Lots of activity.  Saw loons and eagle.  Sunny- mid 70s.
Saw about 2 adult loons with 2 babies at both ends of lake.  2 families of 4 loons.  Sunny.  72 F.
Somewhat windy.  Overcast.  Rain early in day during sailing regatta.
Beautiful- sunny- clear day.  Excellent day on lake.  Many other boats.
Slight drizzle.  Overcast.  Not a great day for a boat ride.
Lake levels continue to drop.  EW milfoil more visible
Moved loon rafts to witner sites.  Low 60s but sunny with big white clouds.
Nice sunny day.  Good boat activity on lake.  Nice afternoon for boat ride.
75 + F.  Excellent night.  Feels like summer.  Saw loons and eagle in pine tree.
Another beautiful day.  Slight chop on water.  Saw 2 loons- north end.
2nd day of fishing season- 8 boats on lake- windy- choppy waves- light clouds- 62 degrees.
Some cottowood "cotton" and oter tree bloom on water- Great day 70 degrees- saw 1 loon- no loon at nesting raft- several fishermen.
Water levels still LOW! warm day around 80 degrees- overcast saw a total of 3 loons.
Nice day- Memorial Day Weekend- decent recreational boat activity- however- somewhat windy.
Slight rain- however fishermen still out- clouds rolling in...storms coming
Slight drizzle- loon on nesting raft- overcast- some rain last few days.
Loon on nest- 3 other loons on lake- 3 eagles ( i adult/2 babies). Awesome day on lake.
Sunny + Beatiful- 2 loons at nest- toatl of 5 loons and 8 eagles sighted.
LOW water levels- Results! 1 baby loon with 2 adult loons- great day- water choppy but still pleasant.
Lake active with boaters and fishermen with sightings of loons and eagles.
Rainy in morning- cloudy with occasional rain during monitoring. Saw 2 loons and lake active with skiers and jet skis.
Wonderful day for boating- Saw 1 baby loon and 5 adult loons.
Warm and muggy- somewhat cloudy- Saw baby loon w/parents on North end of lake.
Overcast in morning- niece swam across lake- more activity on lake with boaters and fishermen.
Lots of rain last few days- Great day on lake- baby loon growing fast- saw 3 adult loons.
Hot day/muggy- lake somewhat choppy- water level better...but still LOW!
Nice day- good activity on lake with power boats- saw loons on North end of lake.
Fall colors full + robust- somewhat windy- beautiful day on lake enjoying the fall colors.

Windy/choppy waters- temperature stratification of water minimal due to winds- recent rains- cooler weather and ice out May 1- 2011. Saw 2 loons near boat landing. About a dozen fishing boats out in bays and coves to avoid wind.
Cooler- highs in mid 60's- rain previous day. Slight bloom on lake. Better activity on lake due to holiday weekend.

Loons on nesting raft. Boat landing quite busy. Water has a more Greenish/Blue color than usualClean Boats/Clean water personnel at landing. The boats on lake mainly fishing. Excellent day for boating and lake activities.
Extreme winds this past week. Loon raft washed ashore and will be relaunched. Slightly overcast in mid 60's. Lake churned up from the high winds.
Several trailers at boat landing. Cloudy- occasional raindrops. Several fishermen on lake. Launching pontoon boat for the year!
Looks like the loons are active on their nest after raft was washed ashore and relaunched. Mostly clear with temperatures in the mid 70's.
Lots of boat traffic due to holiday: skiers- PWC- kayak- sailboat...Loons on nest. saw an additional pair of loons at south end of lake. Slighly overcast in Mid 80's.
Long lake Sunfish Regatta with over a dozen participants entering multiple events. Light drizzle for short period as it was mostly cloudy.
HOT!...but beautiful day on lake. The loons have 2 babies from second nesting session after initial nesting session was disrupted  as raft washed ashore during period of high winds.
Mostly cloudy. More activity on lake than usual...boaters- fishermen- skiers and PWC's. saw 2 eagles perched on trees and loons with set of babies.
Nice day on lake. Sailboat moving along smootly as the slight wind left a ripple on the water. saw the loons raising their babies and an eagle perched high in a tree.

Beautiful day...another eagle atop a tree and again saw the 2 loons with babies. EWM treatment looks to have reduce the problem both in size (acres) and density. Greenish film on lakes surface...slight but noticeable. Sunny- light puffy clouds.
Mostly cloudy -mid 70's- A total of 5 loons on lake plus the 2 babies. Saw a merganser duck with 3 little ducklings. Wind was slight but evident.

Beautiful day- just enough wind for a ripple on the waterbaby loons almost becoming full size. EWM showing up in some of the probelm areas and looks more dense than earlier. However- EWM overall looks much improved from previous year.
Cool in the morning about 50 degrees. Very calm- trees are showing their Fall Colors. Little activity on lake...taking out pontoon for the season in an occasional slight drizzle.
Nice fall afternoon...Lots of good color...probably peak...reflecting on the water. Taking out fishing boat for the season! THE END!

Temperature 35 degrees- ice out on 3/19- launch the loon raft- no loons seen- just a very few birds flying overhead. Slight wind with over cast skies and a water temperature of 39.6 degrees. No visible aquatic plant growth in water. Jeff Carter Mason and Joan Carter assited.
Temperature in upper 50's. Set out the caution marker bouy for the loon raft prior to the fishing opener. Loons were in the vincinity of the loon raft but not active on raft. DNR on lake doing study.
Temperatures in the mid 50's with light winds. AIS chemical treatment being applied with monitoring by Army Corps of Engineering. Loon raft active.
Light winds and temps in mid 60's. Starting to see more aqautic growth on lake which appears to be native. More landowners have docks in and boats ready for the summer season.
Around 80 degrees. Light winds with occasional gusts. More boating activity throughout the day: fishermen and leaisure boaters. Loons are active on the loon raft.
Hot and humid and relatively calm. No loons were seen but did not travel to the loon nesting raft.Light rain earlier in the day.
Light winds with temperatures in the upper 60's. The lake had a rippling effect of waves. Loons active feeding along with a sight of an eagle on a nest near the thoroughfare.
A storm is blowing in. Dark clouds loom in the background. Wildlife activity is non-existent.

Mid 70's and light winds. Cloudy with a slight mist in the air. Long Lake held the Sailboat Regatta today. Sighted baby loon! On Wednesday- lake district commissioners took tour of lake with AIS Chemical Treatment Vendor. Some EWM found but density was reduced and patches also reduced in size.

Gogeous day with temperatures in the low 80's and clear skies. A slight ripple on the water. Saw a toatl of 5 adult loons and a baby loon. Good activity on lake with boaters- skiers- fishermen and PWC's.
Upper 60's. Slightly overcast. Many boaters- skiers- PWC's and "tubers" on lake.

Light winds and slightly overcast. temps in mid 70's. Baby loon on lake with parents. 2 eagles surveying the lake from tall pines. Looked at some aquatic plants poking out of the water which semed to be non-AIS specimens.
Occasional gusts but mostly light winds in the mid 60's. Total sightings of 5 loons and several seagulls. More fishermen than usually seen.

Light winds- clear skies with ocassional cloud and temperatures in low 80's. Activity on lake is low in terms of watercraft. Merganser family of 7 moving along the shoreline. Loons (3 in mid-section of lake) and gulls are active.
Overcast with temps in the low 80's. Baby loon beginning to look mature...especially in size. Activity on lake winding down from the height of the Labor Day Weekend.

Clear fall day around 70 degrees. Fall colors beginning to appear. Lake level is quite low with noticeable shoreline exposed. Some landowners have already pulled boats due to water level...especially near docks.
Loons active on nesting raft. Slight ripple on water. Activity on lake increasing but still light. On June 4th- EWM treatment took place over approximately 45 acres.
Loons on nest. Appears EWM is stressed from earlier chemical treatment.
A little bloom or pollen on lake surface. Water appears to be stirred up from recent rains and winds. Saw a pair of loons with 2 chicks. At other end of lake saw another pair of loons.
Rain earlier in week. Windy today...out for very short time. Divers were on the lake July 8th to hand pull EWM.
Light winds and chop on water. Continued stress on EWM plants from chemical treatment. Loons active with chicks. Eagle in tall pine tree near thoroughfare.
CB/CW Program in force monitoring boats at landing. Cool but nice on lake. Loons- eagles- and mergansers sighted on lake. Have seen fewer mergansers than previous years.
Great day on lake with lots of activity with boating- jet skiing and fishing.
Appears to be more suspended matter in the water with a slight green tint (algae?).There was decent rain overnight which may have added to somewhat murky waters.
Lake level dropping below what I consider normal.
Cool but calm winds- fall colors are beautiful. Some debris and leaves floating on water but minimal amounts.
This is a bonus day for October...Great Weather. EWM Treatment follow up by vendor at 1:00pm.

Memorial Day Weekend! Lots more activity on lake. Fishermen- boaters and landowners  launching boats for the season. A total of 8 trailers at the boat landing (all free of AIS). No activity on the loon raft. Loons in area but not ON the raft.
Overcast with some rain during the day. Pollen floating on the surface of the water especially in the bays and still waters. Temperature in the 70's.

Temps around 60 degrees. Loon nesting on special raft. Still some floating pollen on the water. A few fishermen out. Starting to see some growth of aquatic plants throughout the lake. Clean Lakes- INC. completed the treatment for Eurasion Milfoil on approximately 26 acres.

Nice...actually Beautiful day on lake. Lots of boating activity - fishing- skiing- jet skis..... Almost NO wind for a change. Loons are active on nest and out searching for food. Appears to be a few trailers at boat landing. Saw 2 pairs of loons and an Eagle soaring.

Rain earlier in the day. Dark gray clouds...could rain again? Only 1 other boat out on a Holiday Weekend. Saw a loon out diving. Water somewhat choppy but no white caps. Eagle sighted in Pine Tree near thoroughfare.
Windy. Temps in 60's. Hard to steady the boat. No other boats on lake as weather looks inclement and actually started to drizzle on way back to dock.

Temps around 70 degrees. Winds starting to pick up. A few fishermen out in the bays and coves. AIS trouble spots looking better after treatment. Still not seeing the number of ducks as years before from the boat OR on the shore.

Nice Day! Somewhat cooler but sunny! Probably in the upper 50's. Baby loon sighted with parents. However- only 1 loon sighted as there were 2 eggs. Not too active on lake...probably 'cause it's Wednesday Morning. Taking fishing boat to boat landing to put on trailer.
Mid 60's. Clear + Sunny. Great afternoon to be on the water. Several other boaters had the same idea. Definite reduction of EWM in areas chemically treated or manual (hand) pulling areas.

Around 70 degrees. Slight haze. Peaceful on lake. Light winds at best. Noticeably- the water level has retracted to a low status. Fortunately- it is almost the end of August. However- the area could use a little rain. Several gulls floating around along with the loons at both ends of the lake.
Light winds- clear and sunny around 70 degrees. Gorgeous afternoon. Saw 4 loons and 1 chick. Lake activity winding down after Labor Day. Peaceful and relaxing.
Windy AGAIN!!! Temps around 70 degrees. Not a great day for lake activities like a boat ride. Water a little choppy and the WIND!
Just in and out to do Lake Monitoring. Day after Opening Fishing. 7 trailers at boat landing. Hazy skies with slight chop on water. No activity at Loon Raft launched a week earlier.

Launching boats for the season. Temps in mid 60's with light winds. Loons active. Water looks excellent with light pollen floating on water at some shorelines. Long Lake was chemically treated for Eurasion water milfoil this week.

Water chemistry today. Temps around 70 with light winds. The loon raft is occupied with loons on nest near boat landing. Some light pollen is evident on the water. Seeing more activity with boating and fishing.

Temps in mid 60's. Nice afternoon. Windy earlier. Could not tell with vegetation on Loon raft if it was occupied. Water appears a little stirred up due to the winds. Hearing some good reports on fishing...especially walleye.

Yes- it's a Holiday Weekend. Lots of activity on Long Lake...both on the water and at the shoreline. Temps in mid 70's. Water looks Great. A family of mergansers travelling at the shoreline. The areas treated for EWM appear to be successful...at least for now.

Water level seems to be dropping. Yes we need rain. Lake district trying to have Long Lake Dam closed to 1 inch. Loon hatch successful with 2 baby loons off the loon raft. Temps in mid 70's. Great day to be on water. Saw eagles perching in tall hemlocks. Slight greenish tint to water but very acceptable.
Lake levels keep dropping. Cloudy earlier...but clear now. Just making excursion on lake for water chemistry.

Water levels are dropping drastically. One of the lowest levels EVER! Temps in mid 60's. Loons and loon chicks active searching for food. Fairly cloudy/overcast but still nice. (Rained yesterday 08/07/15)

Somewhat windy. Temps in mid 70's. Loons active at both ends of lake. Lon chicks are growing fast...about 2/3 adult size. Water levels QUITE CONCERNING being so low. Lake district has contacted WVIC for support. Family of mergansers playing on log at shoreline.

Overcast and cloudy. Temps low 60's. Eagle perched in pine tree by thoroughfare. EWM in treated areas (chemical + hand pulling) appear to be successful (reduction). The loons are very active and ALWAYS fun to watch.

column1: NOTE: Pulling boats out September 19th due to low water levels...Disturbing! Earliest date EVER! (There's confirmation of a  beaver dam in thoroughfare between Big Sand Lake and Long Lake.)

column2: Windy + rainy last night. It's been windy past few days. Light waves due to a brisk breeze. Opening day of fishing. 16 boat trailers at landing. About 57 degrees...cooler on the water. Seems like water has been stirred up by the recent winds?
Windy earlier- slight winds now- About 70 degrees. Saw loon on nest on Loon Raft. Not much activity on lake for Memorial Day. Water conditions are good.
Light winds in the mid 70's. Tree Pollen on the water....especially at the shoreline. Lots of rain and wind in the past couple of days. Loon still on nest (loon raft).

Clear + Hot (80 degrees). Water calm. Lots of pollen floating on water....bays and shoreline are worse with less current to move pollen. Rain and wind have stirred up lake. Loon on Nest and Eagles in nest near thoroughfare.

Very HOT last few days. Temp in high 70's. Water clarity good but a little less than normal. Maybe all the Holiday Activity on the lake? Saw a pair of loons with baby (appears to be only one). Lots of activity on lake and at shoreline enjoying the lake/water.
Nice afternoon for a boat ride. Saw a total of 4 adult loons and 3 GROWING baby loons. Lake and water were GREAT! Water clarity getting better!!!
Perfect day on the water for ALL activities. Decent activity on lake and at shoreline. Eagles in tree by the thoroughfare.

Absolutely gorgeous! Water is practically flat...no ripples/waves. Very uncommon on Long Lake. Saw loon with babies. Oh how the babies are growing. Water clarity very good. Very clear at the shoreline.
Temp in low 70's. Light ripple on water. Overall water looks good. Saw Eagle and 3 loons. Quite a nice afternoon.
Nice but somewhat cloudy skies. Mid 60's. Water level remains at normal. That's unusual for this time of year. Many years of recent history it would be classified as low in late August.
Great Night. Saw loons at both ends of the lake. Water clarity Excellent. Very little suspended particles.
Another nice night. Water levels holding at NORMAL. In years past- the boats were out by now due to low water levels. Only saw the 3 baby loons. Have the adults left??? Seems a little early.

Water appears to have some tanins as it is brown. Lots of rain + run off in the past month. Most notable when looking at bottom in shallow areas. Launched loon raft. High's in mid 60's. Sunny light winds.
Temp in high 50's. Excessive rain in last month. Lots of run off. Had to pull boat out as dock was underwater. Water still has brown tanin tint. No loons on nest. Babies?
Mid 70's- Light wind + chop on water. Lots of activity on lake with boating- skiing- fishing and shoreline activity. Great day to enjoy the lake. Saw loons- eagles and mergansers.

Out for a morning pontoon boat ride. Temp in the 60's- barely any wind- Saw loons with just one baby. Starting to see more growth of all weeds possibly due to the added nutrients brought in by excessive rain.
Nice day- warm in the mid 70's- good activity on lake for mid-week. Ducks at shoreline- loons feeding in deeper waters. Could see more resurgence of weed growth especially at south end (dam) of lake.

Temp in the 70's- slight wind- water still has a slight brownish tint but fading and becoming more clear. Loons are active with baby....only one seen. Decent activity on lake with all types of boaters.
Mid 60's Several fishermen on lake- good activity of all boat types. Baby loon is getting big. Out with adult loons fishing.Still concerned about EWM regrowth in some areas.
Light winds- activity on lake has decreased over the past couple of weeks. Loons and baby are actively fishing. Water clarity seems to be getting better and brownish tint is dissipating.
Winds are light- nice day on lake. The holiday increases activity. The last BIG weekend. Fishermen are the most abundant today.
Put in Loon Raft today. Calm winds and quite sunny. Loons were on the raft minutes after in was secure. What an experience. Water quality was superior and very clear on the surface.
Wind was light with some gusts. Slight drizzle at times. Temperature in Mid-60's. Loon on raft. Only fishermen out at this time. Weather could be nicer.
Slight brownish-green tint to water as plant growth is booming. big rains on 6/17. Water still looked OK. Eagle in big hemlock stalking prey. A few boats are out exploring the lake.

Mid 80's. Slight chop on water. Fourth of July brings out great activity on lake from skiers to pontooning to kayaking and many people enjoying time at the shoreline. Nice to see landowners enjoying the lake. Great Day!

Busy on lake. Good Activity. Light winds and high around 80 degrees. Again- all different types of water activities are present. Water in some of the bays seems a little stagnant and still but no issues.

Again- a little choppy on lake. Any wind out of the south west creates waves as it travels long distances on Long Lake. 2 Loon babies are out with adults. Water very clear especially at the shoreline.
Baby loons are growing and learning to dive. A few boats out fishing by thoroughfare. Eagle in tree near the boat landing. Water quality is still great.
Overcast. Light drizzle when returning to dock. EWM very noticeable along with other aquatic plants. Good growth is evident but concerned on EWM issue.

Good Activity on lake all holiday weekend. Loons are active with babies. The young loons are venturing a little further away from the parents. Milfoil and Aquatic Plants are getting quite dense in some areas.

Ice out on May 3rd. Launched Loon Raft. No Loons in-sight. Temp in high 50's. Water level extremely high. A couple of inches of rain over the weekend. Great day to launch loon raft as only a slight wind. Water too high to put in some docks....ours for one.
Heavy rain Saturday early morning. slight winds- light pollen in/on water (noticeable but not bad). Loons on the nest!

Temp in 70's. Loons active near boat landing- Eurasian water milfoil is active and some areas of higher density- milfoil should not affect the casual boater but is most noticeable at the dam end of lake. Noice to see more activity on lake and at water's edge.
Water level staying high (great news)- Lake is very active- nice evening for pontoon ride.
Loons out with babies- milfoil still active and matting in some areas- Eagles in nest at thoroughfare.
Water level is great staying high....usually it has dropped over a foot and goes from High to Normal heading to Low by this time of year. This is nice for docking boats.
Loon babies are growing. Water looks great but reads a lower clarity. Milfoil still is active and becoming more dense in areas.
Water levels still high. The rock we use to measure levels is still completely submersed. Nice afternoon to be on water. Activity on lake is good for late August.
Water is near high water level at dam. Nice consistency of water level this summer. Good activity on lake for Labor Day weekend. Loons are active and saw some deer near the water.

Very calm- some algae floating on top of water..making swirls. Looks a little disturbing but should rectify itself with a little breeze or boating activity. All loons are practically the same size. Actually- very enjoyable for a pontoon ride.
